# A--Z Git & GitHub Commands (Complete Guide)

This document lists the full set of essential **Git & GitHub commands**
alphabetically from **A to Z**, along with clear descriptions.\
These are the commands you will use while working with Git locally and
interacting with GitHub.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  A

### **git add**

Add files to the staging area.

    git add <file>

### **git apply**

Apply a patch file.

    git apply <patch>

### **git archive**

Create a zip/tar archive of your repo.

    git archive --format=zip HEAD > code.zip

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  B

### **git bisect**

Binary search to find which commit introduced a bug.

    git bisect start

### **git branch**

Create, list, or delete branches.

    git branch <branch-name>

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  C

### **git checkout**

Switch branches or restore files.

    git checkout <branch>

### **git clone**

Clone a GitHub repository.

    git clone <repo-url>

### **git commit**

Save changes to history.

    git commit -m "message"

### **git config**

Set user-level or repo-level configuration.

    git config user.name "Name"

### **git clean**

Remove untracked files.

    git clean -f

### **git cherry-pick**

Apply a commit from another branch.

    git cherry-pick <commit-hash>

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  D

### **git diff**

View file changes.

    git diff

### **git difftool**

Open changes in an external diff tool.

    git difftool

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  F

### **git fetch**

Download changes from remote without merging.

    git fetch

### **git format-patch**

Create patch files from commits.

    git format-patch -1 HEAD

### **git fsck**

Verify repository integrity.

    git fsck

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  G

### **git grep**

Search text in tracked files.

    git grep "<text>"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  H

### **git help**

Get help for any command.

    git help <command>

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  I

### **git init**

Initialize a new repository.

    git init

### **.gitignore**

Specify which files to ignore.

    touch .gitignore

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  L

### **git log**

View commit history.

    git log

### **git ls-files**

List tracked files.

    git ls-files

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  M

### **git merge**

Merge branches.

    git merge <branch>

### **git mv**

Move or rename files.

    git mv old new

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  N

### **git notes**

Add notes to commits.

    git notes add -m "text"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  P

### **git pull**

Fetch + merge changes from remote.

    git pull

### **git push**

Upload commits to GitHub.

    git push

### **git prune**

Clean unreachable objects.

    git prune

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  R

### **git rebase**

Reapply commits on top of another base.

    git rebase <branch>

### **git remote**

Manage remote repository connections.

    git remote add origin <url>

### **git reset**

Undo commits or restore files.

    git reset --hard

### **git restore**

Restore changed/deleted files.

    git restore <file>

### **git revert**

Create a new commit that undoes a previous commit.

    git revert <commit>

### **git rm**

Remove tracked files.

    git rm <file>

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  S

### **git stash**

Temporarily store changes.

    git stash

### **git status**

Show working directory status.

    git status

### **git switch**

Modern branch switch command.

    git switch <branch>

### **git show**

Display a commit or object.

    git show <commit>

### **git submodule**

Manage submodules.

    git submodule add <repo>

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  T

### **git tag**

Create/list version tags.

    git tag <tagname>

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  U

### **git update-index**

Manually update the staging area.

    git update-index

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  V

### **git --version**

Check Git version.

    git --version

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  W

### **git worktree**

Use multiple working directories.

    git worktree add <path> <branch>

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ðŸ”  Z

There are **no Git commands** starting with Z.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ðŸ“Œ Conclusion

This README contains every essential Git/GitHub command from **A to
Z**.\
You can directly use it in your GitHub repository for documentation or
learning.
